Load Packages & Data & Preview Initial Data

library(tidyverse)
library(dplyr)
library(stringr)
library(tidyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(NLP)
TournamentStats <- read.csv("Data_RegEx3.csv", header = T)
tail(TournamentStats)

Creation of New Year Variable Based on First Four Digits of tourney_id

StatsWYear <- TournamentStats %>% mutate(year = str_sub(tourney_id, 1,4));
tail(StatsWYear)

Creation of Sets based on Score Variables

Creation of setsplayed Variable

SetsPlayed <- FinalSets %>% mutate(setsplayed = as.character((rowSums(!is.na(FinalSets[8:12])))))
tail(SetsPlayed)

Creation of Density Plot of Minutes Played by Number of Sets Played

SetsPlayed2 <- SetsPlayed %>% filter(as.integer(setsplayed) > 0)
ggplot(SetsPlayed2, aes(x = minutes, fill = setsplayed)) +
  geom_density( color = NA) +
  theme(legend.position = "top") +
  labs(fill="Sets Played") +
  ylab("Density") +
  xlab("Minutes Played") +
  ggtitle("Density Plots of Minutes Played Per Number of Sets Played")

Interpretive Statement for the Above Density Plot: In this density plot we can examine the relationship between sets played and minutes played. Based on the results of this plot, we can see that, generally, an increase of sets results in an increase of minutes played. Also, we see as the number of sets played increases, the level of variation for the minutes played increases.

Creation of Boxplot of Winner’s Age by Tournament Name

SetsPlayed$tourney_name[SetsPlayed$tourney_name=="Us Open"]<-"US Open"

ggplot(SetsPlayed, aes(x = tourney_name, y = winner_age, color = tourney_name)) + 
  geom_boxplot() +
  scale_color_discrete(name = "Tournament Name") +
  ylab("Age of Winner") + 
  xlab("Tournament Name") +
  ggtitle("Boxplot Age of Winner in Grand Slam Events")

Interpretive Statement for the Above Box Plots: In this plot, we examine the distribution of ages in each tournament. Overall, the distribution of ages looks very similar among different tournaments with a median age of around 27-28 across tournaments. It’s also incredible to see that among the tournaments there is a wide range of ages from people as young as teenagers participating to people who are over 40 years old.
